      <h2 id="macro-pulse">GET /macro</h2>
      <p><strong>Macro conditions</strong> — a daily deterministic composite of net liquidity (Fed balance sheet − TGA − RRP), the dollar index, real yields, the 2s10s curve, M2 and VIX, combined with the upcoming high-impact calendar and recent intel. The <code>/macro</code> response always carries the composite and drivers; per-asset bias is included only when its supporting model is available and is otherwise explicitly withheld.</p>
      <p>The top-level <code>current</code> object contains the latest report. Add <code>?history=N</code> (Pro, max 30) to include prior snapshots; free accounts receive the current report only. Bias and conviction are nullable and explicitly withheld when supporting data is insufficient.</p>
